snippet.textDisplay: I don't know... I understand where this fan is coming from, but it's not really her/his business. If Shane is happy with his weight then it's really none of your business. Shit, it's none of your business even if he is unhappy because he wasn't talking about it to you. Don't get me wrong, now he is talking about it and he left the youtube comments open for us to discuss but you get my point. He wasn't talking about it to us or his friends so it wasn't anybody's business. It's basic, general respect... If someone doesn't want to talk about something that is a part of their personal life, you respect them and you keep it moving. It's not up to you to dictate or comment or even show pitty. Some people don't want the pitty, some people are happy the way that they are and I know, it's very hard for Americans to understand for some reason, you guys love to invade people's privacy and be disrespectful to each other for some reason, I don't know maybe you think you're entitled. It is SHANE'S choice, not Ryland, not Morgan not us not nobody, SHANE... He is a mature adult, nobody is "enabling" him. If you're an adult and you're still being "enabled" to make choices that you don't want to make, you clearly have some growing up to do. By that logic, the person who "enabled" the 200 pound person to eat so much food that they are dangerously obese was "enabled" by the 200 pound person to "enable" him to keep eating. SO it's still the 200 pound person's fault that they're 200 pounds. I'm just saying, let people be people, focus on your own life.
